article.headline: Langhorne scores 30 to lead No. 9 Maryland thumping
article.linkText: Langhorne scores 30 to lead No. 9 Maryland thumping
article.story:
COLLEGE PARK, Md. (AP) -- Crystal Langhorne scored a season-high 30 points, and No. 9 Maryland beat Mount St. Mary's 102-53 Sunday.

Jade Perry had a career-high 23 points and 13 rebounds, Shay Doron scored 18 and Ashleigh Newman added 10 for the Terrapins (6-1), who scored at least 100 points for the second straight game and third time this season.

Brianna Gauthier led the Mountaineers (2-3) with 14 points.

Langhorne averaged 14.2 points in the first six games for the Terrapins, and her previous season-high was 17. The sophomore scored 21 of her 30 points in the opening half, going 10-for-10 from the field. She missed her first shot with one minute gone in the second half.

Maryland charged to an 11-0 lead 2:57 in on its way to a 56-22 halftime lead. The Terps shot 63.2 percent in the half and 56.2 percent overall.

The Terps limited Mount St. Mary's to 25.3 percent shooting and outrebounded the Mountaineers 58-39.
